      • runTcl

        public static List<String> runTcl(Path outputLog,
                                  Path tclScript,
                                  boolean verbose,
                                  String[] environ,
                                  File runDir)
        method to run a Tcl script in vivado
        Parameters:
        outputLog - Path to the log file that vivado will generate
        tclScript - Path to the Tcl script that will be run
        verbose - If true vivado command line and std.out/err will be printed to std.out
        environ - array of strings, each element of which has environment variable settings in the format name=value, or null if the subprocess should inherit the environment of the current process.
        runDir - the working directory of the subprocess, or null if the subprocess should inherit the working directory of the current process.
        Returns:
        the contents of the log file as a list of strings

      • writeBitstream

        public static List<String> writeBitstream(Path dcp,
                                          Path bitFile,
                                          boolean hasEncryptedIP,
                                          String tclPreamble)
        Run Vivado's `write_bitstream` on the provided DCP file to generate a bit file at the specified location.
        Parameters:
        dcp - The DCP file from which to generate a bitstream.
        bitFile - The location of the bit file to generate
        hasEncryptedIP - Flag indicating if the provided DCP contains encrypted IP and was written by RapidWright such that it needs to be loaded with a Tcl script.
        tclPreamble - String of Tcl commands to run before write_bitstream (null for no preamble).
        Returns:
        The output of Vivado as a list of Strings

      • writeBitstream

        public static List<String> writeBitstream(Path dcp,
                                          Path bitFile,
                                          boolean hasEncryptedIP,
                                          String tclPreamble,
                                          String rmCell)
        Run Vivado's `write_bitstream` on the provided DCP file to generate a bit file at the specified location.
        Parameters:
        dcp - The DCP file from which to generate a bitstream.
        bitFile - The location of the bit file to generate
        hasEncryptedIP - Flag indicating if the provided DCP contains encrypted IP and was written by RapidWright such that it needs to be loaded with a Tcl script.
        tclPreamble - String of Tcl commands to run before write_bitstream (null for no preamble).
        rmCell - The name of the reconfigurable module cell if this is a DFX bitstream.
        Returns:
        The output of Vivado as a list of Strings
